	(2)	The making of loans through mortgage lenders to eligible borrowers or qualified sponsors;
	(3)	The allocation to mortgage lenders of money made available under this subpart; and
	(4)	The participation by mortgage lenders as originators and processors of loans on behalf of the administration under this subpart.



	(b)  The administration may adopt rules necessary or convenient for the operation of the housing loan programs established under this subpart. [L 1997, c 350, pt of §2; am L 2005, c 196, §26(a)]
